      "id": "bd0d3155-21f3-4317-9a42-13fe67bfae48",
      "type": "markdown",
      "text": "A tiling or __tessellation__ of a flat surface is the covering of a [[plane (mathematics)]] using one or more [[geometric shape]]s, called tiles, with no overlaps and no gaps. In [[mathematics]], tessellations can be generalized to [[high-dimensional spaces]] and a variety of geometries - [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tessellation wikipedia]"
